The paper deals with the challenge of adversarial learning, which is a topic that spans multiple sub-categories in computer science. However, the focus on visually interpreting and analyzing the robustness of models suggests that the paper is most likely to belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with adversarial malware, which falls under the sub-category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). Additionally, the use of self-organizing maps and visual means of superimposing adversarial and natural variants suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
